lab1a.c:
	In this source file, I implement each functionality as lab instruction indicates. The program has two options. 
./lab1a will execute a simple terminal I/O.
./lab1a --shell will pass information between two processes.

Makefile:
	This make include three options. make(default), make clean and make dist
	make(defalut): Create an execautable lab1a with Wall and Wextra flag
	make clean: Remove the execautable as well as the tarball
	dist : Create a tarball for submission including lab1a.c Makefile README

README : This file contains information about each files as well as reference source used.

Reference:
	For non-echo and one character mode:
		 https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Noncanon-Example.html
	Pipe information :  
		 http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/pipe.2.html
	kill(3) : 
		 https://linux.die.net/man/3/kill
	poll(2) :
		 http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/poll.2.html
	More information about processes : 
	         http://cs241.cs.illinois.edu/wikibook/processes-part-1-introduction.html
	fork() : 
		 http://cs241.cs.illinois.edu/wikibook/forking-part-1-introduction.html
